	<img width="1038" height="576" src="wp-content/uploads/027_YELLOWPERIL_4254X2836-1038x576.jpg" class="attachment-twentyfourteen-full-width size-twentyfourteen-full-width wp-post-image" alt="" srcset="wp-content/uploads/027_YELLOWPERIL_4254X2836-1038x576.jpg 1038w, wp-content/uploads/027_YELLOWPERIL_4254X2836-672x372.jpg 672w" sizes="(max-width: 1038px) 100vw, 1038px" />	</div>

	
	<header class="entry-header">
				<div class="entry-meta">
			<span class="cat-links"><a href="category/archive/index.html" rel="category tag">Archive</a></span>
		</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
		<h1 class="entry-title">Anti-Japanese post cards, c. 1942</h1>
		<div class="entry-meta">
			<span class="post-format">
				<a class="entry-format" href="type/image/index.html">Image</a>
			</span>

			<span class="entry-date"><a href="index.html@p=170" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2014-07-29T16:54:39+00:00">July 29, 2014</time></a></span> <span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="author/mp233/index.html" rel="author">Mark Tseng Putterman</a></span></span>
						<span class="comments-link"><a href="index.html@p=170#respond">Leave a comment</a></span>
			
					</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	<div class="entry-content">
		<p><a href="wp-content/uploads/027_YELLOWPERIL_4254X2836.jpg"><img class="wp-image-171 size-full alignnone" src="wp-content/uploads/027_YELLOWPERIL_4254X2836.jpg" alt="Archivist of the &quot;Yellow Peril&quot; Exhibit Photography, 8/21/06 &amp; 8" width="4254" height="2836" srcset="wp-content/uploads/027_YELLOWPERIL_4254X2836.jpg 4254w, wp-content/uploads/027_YELLOWPERIL_4254X2836-300x200.jpg 300w, wp-content/uploads/027_YELLOWPERIL_4254X2836-1024x682.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 4254px) 100vw, 4254px" /></a></p>
<p>During the Second World War, popular forms of propaganda quelled American fears and bolstered support for a war without mercy.</p>
<p>The right-hand image is accompanied by a couplet:</p>
<blockquote><p>&#8220;Here hangs the pelt of a Jap</p>
<p>Who mistook a Yank for a sap</p>
<p>He never deserved to be preserved</p>
<p>So we just kept his hide and his cap&#8221;</p></blockquote>
<p><em>From the <a style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;" href="http://www.nyu-apastudies.org/2012/the-yoshio-kishi-irene-yah-ling-sun-collection/" target="_blank">Yoshio Kishi and Irene Yah-Ling Sun Collection</a>; Fales Library and Special Collections, New York University Libraries. </em></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

